pr_body:
possible fix for Extensions ignored in YIN format.

Steps to reproduce: 

**amodule.yang**

``` module amodule {
    yang-version 1;
  namespace "http://test.com/amodule";
  prefix am;

  import bmodule {
    prefix bm;
  }  
  container test {
        uses bm:test;
  }
} ```

**bmodule.yang**
``` module bmodule {
    yang-version 1;
  namespace "http://test.com/bmodule";
  prefix bm;

  import extension {
    prefix ext;
  }

  grouping test {
        ext:abc "some value";
        leaf a {
            type string;
        }
  }
}```

**extension.yang**
``` module extension {
    yang-version 1;
  namespace "http://test.com/ext";
  prefix ext;

  extension abc {
      argument path;
      description
        "extension abc";
    }
}```

> pyang -f yin -o amodule.yin amodule.yang
> 
> .\bmodule.yin:13:  error: no module with the namespace "http://test.com/ext" is imported

Django looks in the jinja2 subdirectory, so this should work out of the box with the jinja2 template engine, if APP_DIRS is set to true in the template settings, i.e.

```
TEMPLATES = [
    {
        'BACKEND': 'django.template.backends.jinja2.Jinja2',
        'DIRS': ['[site template dir]'],
        'APP_DIRS': True,
    },
]
```

